The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Colgate Palmolive net profit dips 25%

 Oct. 31 (PTI): Colgate Palmolive India Ltd has reported a 24.94 per cent decline in net profit at Rs 23.18 crore for the quarter ended September 30 compared with Rs 30.88 crore for the corresponding quarter last year.

 However, total income increased 17.5 per cent to Rs 338.25 crore from Rs 287.87 crore during the same quarter a year ago, the company has informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 The companys board has declared a first interim dividend of Rs 4.25 per equity share of Rs 10 each for 2006-07.

 Hindustan Zinc 

 Hindustan Zinc Ltd has posted over six-fold increase in net profit at Rs 1,298 crore for the quarter ended September 30 compared with Rs 196 crore for the same quarter last fiscal.

 The total income increased to Rs 2,487 crore from Rs 706 crore in the corresponding quarter a year ago.

 Sterling Biotech

 Sterling Biotech Ltd has posted a 27 per cent increase in net profit at Rs 36.43 crore for the quarter ended September 30 against Rs 28.64 crore for the same quarter last year.

 Total income rose 32 per cent to Rs 162.08 crore for the third quarter this year from Rs 123.06 crore in the year-ago period.

 BPCL net 

 Bharat Petroleum Corporation Ltd has reported a net profit of Rs 1,258.5 crore for the quarter ended September 30 against Rs 18.8 crore for the corresponding quarter last year. Total income stood at Rs 26,738.1 crore compared with Rs 17,190.1 crore in the year-ago period. 

 Hinduja TMT 

 Hinduja TMT has reported a profit after tax of Rs 508.19 crore for the quarter ended September 30 against Rs 12.09 crore in the corresponding quarter last fiscal.




